This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of person re-identification, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of a generative adversarial network (GAN) also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of novel discriminators and loss functions, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of multiple datasets and the evaluation of performance also suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the issue of robustness in person re-identification, which could fall under the cybersecurity (cs.CR) sub-category.
